City Juma Masjid, Kannur City One of the biggest and oldest Masjid in Kannur District.
A special lamp is lit in the Masjid at the beginning of every Arabic month. This practice has been going on for about 250 years. It is still being observed without any damage. Earlier during the Arakkal reign, a person would go from the Masjid to the palace and after confirming that he had seen the moonrise, he would inform the Masjid khatib and immediately light a special light in the Masjid. A light has been installed on the top of the Masjid in the shape of moon. On that day all the people of  Kannur district will be near the Masjid.

Kannur City is a residential suburb of Kannur Town. This place is called a 'city' because it was the ancient capital of the Kannur town.[citation needed] It is different from the actual city of Kannur, which is the administrative head quarters of the Kannur District. Kannur City is the home of the Arakkal Palace, the Mappila Bay and many ancient historic mosques. The City Juma Masjid in Kannur City and the Moideen mosque at Ayikkara are examples of such mosques of historic significance. Other places falling within the limits of Kannur City are Ayikkara, Chirakkalkulam, Thayyil, Marakkarkandy, Naaluvayal, Anjukkandy, Kuruva, Anayiduck, Kochipalli and Neerchal.

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
This is Baghdad. Not the Baghdad of the Arabic stories my mother told me. Baghdad in God's own country. It is only nine kilometers from Kannur city. Yes, the village of Baileel in Kannur, the land of the sheikhs, is also nicknamed the Baghdad of India. This is also the resting place of the rarest migratory parrots in Kerala. The 457th Uruz Mubarak of Shaikh Khausul Aslam Shaikh Abdul Qadir Sani, who rested here, is being held on Friday and Saturday. Many people from inside and outside Kerala will come to the shrine to refresh his memory

From Yama to Chirakal...
The history of Sheikh Abdul Qadir Sani begins with Sheikh Uthman, a descendant of Abu Bakr Siddiq, the first disciple of the Prophet Muhammad and the first Caliph. Osman was the Sultan of Hamadan in Yemen. 450 years ago he left everything from the palace of Hamadan and came to Valapattanam in Kerala. He was given a warm welcome at Chirakkal Palace. Meanwhile he had a divine vision. That your base is here and that you marry and live here. So he married the daughter of Valapatnam Khasi. Soon Abdulqadir Sani was born.

Shaikh Abdul Qadir Sani and Bhaileel..

The history of this place is clarified in the Baheel Maulud book prepared by Abdul Aziz Maulavi, one of the Makhdums of Ponnani. Abdul Qadir Sani had many miracles in his childhood and was invited and given a great position in the Chirakkal palace. On the day of her 15th birthday, Suhra Vardi met Sheikh Mahmudul Qabushani, a famous sheikh and scholar of Tawreeq. With that, Abdulqadir Sani opened the door to the spiritual path. Lord Chirakal prepared all the facilities but left them all and found a place outside without any noise of the princely kingdom. History says that this is how the name Baheel came about.

Baghdad, India

Abdul Qadir Sani came to mean Abdul Qadir II who came after Sultanul Auliya Abdul Qadir Jilani from Baghdad. Zani means second. That's how Bagheel got its name as Bagdad in India. Near the big maqam, more than 40 auliyas who were disciples of Abdul Qadir Sani and more than 40 sheikhs are resting in small maqams.

Features of the release

The life of the Mahanavars who lived 453 years ago was exemplary. It is known as the Walaif of Baheel Shaikh. It still exists today. Short fixed surahs in prayers, special prayer before Subh prayer, Aurad and congregational prayer in the inner mosque after Subh until sunrise. Asr prayer and Aurad, Dhikr halqa after Maghrib on Thursday, Friday and Monday nights, Taraweeh prayer at 1 o'clock after midnight in Ramadan, and Tauba after Jumuah prayer are unique here. Khatmul Qur'an Uruz is held here on the 16th of the Arabic month of Dulqaad. By Sheikh Abdul Qadir Sani. Baheel Shaikh is the descendants of his daughter known as family. At each time one of the family is appointed as Shaykh for life as stipulated in the family's record. Maniyur Ahmed Muslyar is currently in the position of Shaikh.
